Profit Prediction from 50 startups¶

Prepare a prediction model for profit of 50_startups data.

1. Do transformations for getting better predictions of profit and make a table containing R^2 value for each prepared model.
2. Do proper exploratory Data Analysis.
3. Upload the Code in the github
4. Share the HTML jupyter notebook in the mail.
5. Use notion.io for process tracking and timeline.

Dataset Descriptions -

R&D Spend -- Research and devolop spend in the past few years Administration -- spend on administration in the past few years Marketing Spend -- spend on Marketing in the past few years State -- states from which data is collected Profit -- profit of each state in the past few years

outliers = []
def detect_outliers_iqr(data):
    data = sorted(data)
    q1 = np.percentile(data, 25)
    q3 = np.percentile(data, 75)
    # print(q1, q3)
    IQR = q3-q1
    lwr_bound = q1-(1.5*IQR)
    upr_bound = q3+(1.5*IQR)
    # print(lwr_bound, upr_bound)
    for i in data: 
        if (i<lwr_bound or i>upr_bound):
            outliers.append(i)
    return outliers# Driver code
profit_outliers = detect_outliers_iqr(data['Profit'])

###Model 1
def linear_pred_model(data):
    x = data[[columns[0],columns[2]]]
    y = data[columns[-1]]
    model1 =LinearRegression()
    train_model1 = model1.fit(x,y)
    pred = train_model1.predict(x)
    print("The accuracy is..",round(r2_score(pred,y)*100,2),"%")
    print("The Error is..",m.sqrt(mean_squared_error(pred,y)))

###Model 2
##### Instead of running the same code many times we can create a model 

def linear_pred_model1(data,test_data_size):
    ### Spliting of test and train data
    train_data,test_data = train_test_split(data,test_size=test_data_size)
    
    #### Assigning dependent and independent values from train data
    x_train = train_data[[columns[0],columns[2]]]
    y_train = train_data[columns[-1]]
    
    ### Model creation
    model = LinearRegression()
    train_model = model.fit(x_train,y_train,)
    print("Training of Model is Done...")
    
    #### Assigning dependent and independent values from test data
    x_test = test_data[[columns[0],columns[2]]]
    y_test = test_data[columns[-1]]
    
    ### Predicting of accuracy 
    print("The accuracy by r2 score is..",round(r2_score(y_test,train_model.predict(x_test))*100,2),"% for the model with test size",test_data_size)

##### From comparing all the model 20% test data and 80% train data has the highest prediction accuracy so we can select that

def pred_profit(rd_spending,marketing_spending,test_data_size):
    ### Spliting of test and train data
    ### Spliting of test and train data
    train_data,test_data = train_test_split(data,test_size=test_data_size,random_state=123)
    
    #### Assigning dependent and independent values from train data
    x_train = train_data[[columns[0],columns[2]]]
    y_train = train_data[columns[-1]]
    
    ### Model creation
    model = LinearRegression()
    train_model = model.fit(x_train,y_train,)
    print("Training of Model is Done...")
    
    ### Storing the coefficient and intercept from the model to predict the output
    train_model_coef = train_model.coef_
    train_model_intercept = train_model.intercept_
    
    result = round(((train_model_coef[0] * rd_spending)+(train_model_coef[1] * marketing_spending) + train_model_intercept).flatten()[0],2)
    
    ### Printing the delivery time 
    print("The predicted Profit for R&D Spending {},Marketing Spending {} is ... {}".format(rd_spending,marketing_spending,result))
